Carlos Heredia Fontana (born in 28 September 1998) is a Spanish-born Dominican professional footballer who plays as a winger for Polish I Liga side Miedź Legnica. He is a Dominican Republic international, and began his professional career playing for Wolverhampton Wanderers.


== Career ==
Heredia joined Wolverhampton Wanderers in 2017 from English club Milton Keynes Dons. He was released at the end of the 2018–19 season.Following his release from the Premier League side, Heredia signed a contract with Miedź Legnica lasting until 2023. He made his professional debut for the club in a 1-0 defeat to Stal Mielec, replacing Krzysztof Danielewicz.


== International career ==
On 9 September 2018, Heredia made his debut for Dominican Republic  in the qualifying rounds of the CONCACAF Nations League against Bonaire in a 5-0 victory, scoring the fifth goal.


=== International goals ===
Scores and results list Dominican Republic's goal tally first.


